Straight answers on coatings, PPF, and more

Your Questions, Answered

Whats the difference between wax and ceramic coating?

Wax lasts a few weeks. Ceramic coating bonds to your paint for years. It resists scratches, stains, and UV damageplus water beads right off. Less upkeep, better protection.

Do I need paint correction before ceramic coating?

If your paint has swirl marks, dull spots, or light scratches, yes we recommend at least a one-step polish before applying ceramic. Coatings lock in whatever ’s underneath, so we always aim for a clean, corrected surface first.

Which Is Better - Ceramic Coating or PPF?

PPF provides physical protection against chips and scratches. Ceramic coating offers easier cleaning and UV protection. Many customers choose PPF on high-impact areas and ceramic everywhere else.

How Do I Maintain My Ceramic Coating?

Simple maintenance washes every 2-3 weeks. Use pH-neutral soap, avoid automatic car washes. We offer annual maintenance service to keep coating performing like new.

Can PPF and ceramic coating be applied together?

Absolutely. PPF protects against impact damage like rock chips, while ceramic coating adds slickness, UV resistance, and makes cleaning easier. We apply ceramic coating on top of the film for maximum gloss and protection.

Will Ceramic Coating Fix Scratches?

No, ceramic coating enhances and protects existing paint. We perform paint correction before coating to remove scratches. The coating then preserves that corrected finish.

How Long Does PPF Last?

XPEL paint protection film lasts 7-10 years with proper care. It ’s self-healing, removable, and comes with manufacturer warranty. Protects against rock chips permanently.

What's Included in Your Full Detail Service?

Our Full Detail includes both exterior and interior services. For the exterior, we do hand wash, ceramic wax application, paint decontamination, rim cleaning, and tire shine. Interior service covers complete vacuum, shampooing of carpets and seats, dashboard cleaning, and detailed attention to all surfaces including cup holders and AC vents. Our Signature package adds clay bar treatment, paint correction, and steam cleaning for deeper restoration.

Do You Offer Same-Day Auto Detailing Service?

Yes, we often can accommodate same-day appointments in San Jose and surrounding areas, depending on schedule availability. For best results, we recommend booking 1-2 days in advance. Contact us for current availability in your area.

How Long Does Detailing Take?

A complete detail typically takes 4-6 hours, depending on your vehicle ’s size and condition. Our express maintenance package takes about 2 hours. We provide time estimates when booking and keep you updated throughout the process.
